Notes on dlt and DAG changes:

The daily ingestion has been set up for all the sectors. I made one minor change in the DAGs and one for the dlt script.

The schedule in the DAGs have been changed to "1 22 * * 1-5" from "0 2 * * 2-6". Airflow orchestrated run times at around 2:00 am EST.

The previous dlt scripts included this line:

RUN_DATE = (datetime.now() - pd.tseries.offsets.BDay(1)).strftime("%Y-%m-%d")

This line causes the script to pull data from the last recorded business day. I made this decision then because when I initially tested out the APIs, it would not work on the "current" day.
I must have tried pulling the record on a weekend, which might have reported an error, as the markets are only closed and recorded on weekdays. 

I changed that one line in the dlt scripts instead:

RUN_DATE = pendulum.now("America/New_York").strftime("%Y-%m-%d")

Now, the markets will be synced with the Eastern Time Zone and an hour after the markets close. I don't know how quickly FMP updates its data set, but I believe an hour is a considerable buffer after the markets close.

